Side effects are ignored when a refactoring is proposed for IDE0290.

```
class C
{
	public int A;
	public int B;

public C(int value)
	{
		B = ++value;
		A = ++value;
	}
}
```

The proposed refactoring breaks that code:

```
class C(int value)
{
	public int A = ++value;
	public int B = ++value;
}
```

The following refactoring _might_ be proposed instead, though it's highly subjective whether the developer would consider it better or worse than the original code:

```
class C(int value)
{
	public int B = ++value;
	public int A = ++value;
}
```

